CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 24, 1958, pg. 7 reads: "Checking Parcels - Mrs. Edith Foy has the necessary personality and patience to be in charge of the parcel checking and returns department at the new Treasure Island Department Store, Broad and Larimer, in East Liberty. Here, exchanging an item for a customer, Mrs. Foy displays the winning smile so necessary to her job. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Edith Foy, exchanging item for woman wearing headscarf, holding hand of girl, standing at counter in Treasure Island department store, East Liberty
